@61 = ~Zhentarim Mage~

// Item strings

@200 = ~Montaron's Dagger~
@201 = ~This is one of Montaron's "tools", as he calls them lovingly.

STATISTICS:

Requires:
 3 Strength

Weight: 2~

@202 = ~This is one of Montaron's "tools", as he calls them lovingly.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
– Hit target suffers 2 point of poison damage per second for 5 seconds (Save vs. Poison negates)

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d4+1 (piercing)
Speed Factor: 0
Proficiency Type: Dagger
Type: One–handed
Requires:
 3 Strength

Weight: 2~

@210 = ~Harper Orders~

@211 = ~This was the fool trying to spy on us, exactly how we planned it. According to our information he is not too high up in the Zhentarim and we only needed him to get to his partner, who is likely dead as you read this. Make sure to dump his body far out in the sea, since we saw no need to take extra measures ensuring he won't come back.

R.~

@220 = ~Black Cloak~

@221 = ~Veil of the Untraceable~

@222 = ~This cloak is remarkably unnoticeable – almost suspiciously so. Merely looking at it is discomforting, as if the cloak itself tries to slip from your vision, resisting your gaze.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 3~

@223 = ~This cloak has passed through the hands of many within the Zhentarim, also known as the Black Network. Its original creator is unknown, and the magical protections woven into it have been added gradually over time, often at the behest of new owners. Each addition was designed to aid spies and assassins, making the wearer, as its name suggests, truly untraceable – even by magical means.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Hide in Shadows: +50%
– Move Silently: +50%
– Detect Illusion: +25%
– While hidden or invisible, the wearer is non–detectable by magical means such as Detect Invisibility
– Saving Throws vs Death: +2

Charge abilities:
– Improved Invisibility three times per day
  Duration: 23 rounds
  Area of Effect: The user
  
– Mirror Image three times per day
  Duration: 23 rounds
  Area of Effect: The user

Weight: 3~

// ToB Epilogue
@500 = ~After parting with <CHARNAME>, Montaron disappeared for a time. Soon, the Zhentarim began to suffer losses, their deaths carried out by an almost invisible force. This new enemy cared nothing for riches or power and if his true intentions were anything besides carnage is difficult to discern. When it became apparent that Montaron was responsible, he had already vanished, seemingly disappeared from the world. Those few who catch a glimpse of the solitary halfling living alone, far from civilization — even finding faith in Eldath, the goddess of stillness — would never guess his past. Now only the future will tell if Montaron's change is genuine enough to escape the fate of the faithless.~
@501 = ~After parting with <CHARNAME>, Montaron returned to Athkatla. There he founded a new guild to rival the Shadow Thieves and the Harpers in the city. Quickly he and his guild became the most fearsome in the city and while the Harpers and Shadow Thieves in the city had their numbers thinned Montaron's influence only grew. But it was not long before more and more powerful entities were made aware to the cruelty emanating from Montaron and his guild. After just one year in the city Montaron and his followers were rooted out by fighters and adventurers of great skill and renown. Whether Montaron is still alive and where he might be, is unknown — that is likely how he prefers it. What is certain, though, is that not even the consequences of his actions in death could make Montaron change his cruel ways.~

// EET Dialogue
@600 = ~Bring me Montaron, the fighter/thief.~

